UNIVERSE PLOTS¶

1. Histogram¶

In [1]:
import seaborn as sns
In [2]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [3]:
import numpy as np

Generate Random Data¶

In [6]:
data=np.random.randn(100)

Create a Histogram¶

In [10]:
sns.histplot(data,bins=30,color="blue")
Out[10]:
<AxesSubplot:ylabel='Count'>
In [8]:
plt.title("UNIVARIATE PLOT-HISTOGRAM")
Out[8]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'UNIVARIATE PLOT-HISTOGRAM')
In [11]:
plt.xlabel("VALUE")
Out[11]:
Text(0.5, 0, 'VALUE')
In [12]:
plt.ylabel("FREQUENCY")
Out[12]:
Text(0, 0.5, 'FREQUENCY')
In [13]:
plt.show()
In [15]:
sns.histplot(data,bins=30,color="blue")

2. KDE Plot(Kernel Density Estimate)¶

In [16]:
import seaborn as sns
In [17]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [18]:
import numpy as np

Generate Random Data¶

In [19]:
data=np.random.randn(50)

Create a Histogram¶

In [21]:
sns.kdeplot(data,shade=True,color="red")
Out[21]:
<AxesSubplot:ylabel='Density'>
In [22]:
plt.title("UNIVARIENTE PLOT_KDE")
Out[22]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'UNIVARIENTE PLOT_KDE')
In [24]:
plt.xlabel("Value")
Out[24]:
Text(0.5, 0, 'Value')
In [25]:
plt.ylabel("Density")
Out[25]:
Text(0, 0.5, 'Density')
In [26]:

4.Pair Plot : (Special Bivariate Plot)¶

In [91]:
import pandas as pd

Generate Random Data¶

In [92]:
data = pd.DataFrame({"X": np.random.rand(50),
"Y": np.random.rand(50),
"Z": np.random.rand(50)
})
In [93]:
sns.pairplot(data)
Out[93]:
<seaborn.axisgrid.PairGrid at 0x270990cd9a0>
In [94]:
plt.suptitle("Bivariate Plot - Pair Plot", y=1.02)
Out[94]:
Text(0.5, 1.02, 'Bivariate Plot - Pair Plot')
<Figure size 432x288 with 0 Axes>
In [95]:
sns.pairplot(data)
plt.suptitle("Bivariate Plot - Pair Plot", y=1.02)
plt.show()
